
[1]scammony

   SCAM'MONY, n. [L. scammonia.]

   1. A plant of the genus convolvulus.

   2. A gum resin, obtained from the plant of that name, of a blackish
   gray color, a strong nauseous smell, and a bitter and very acrid taste.
   The best scammony comes from Aleppo, in light spungy masses, easily
   friable. That of Smyrna is black, ponderous, and mixed with extraneous
   matter.
